Spreckels first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Spreckels had a population of 692. The population density was {{convert|5,672.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Spreckels was 426 (61.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 4 (0.6%) [[African Americans|African American]], 9 (1.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 19 (2.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 6 (0.9%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 75 (10.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 153 (22.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 232 persons (33.5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Spreckels CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0673612 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 242 households, out of which 97 (40.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 161 (66.5%) were married-couple households, 11 (4.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 55 (22.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 15 (6.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 44 households (18.2%) were one person, and 23 (9.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.86.<ref name=DP1/> There were 190 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (78.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Spreckels CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0673612 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 195 people (28.2%) under the age of 18, 32 people (4.6%) aged 18 to 24, 166 people (24.0%) aged 25 to 44, 169 people (24.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 130 people (18.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 97.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 260 housing units at an average density of {{convert|2,131.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 242 (93.1%) were occupied. Of these, 172 (71.1%) were owner-occupied, and 70 (28.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===

At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], Spreckels had a population of 673. The population density was {{convert|5,509.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Spreckels was 483 (71.8%) White, 0 (0.0%) African American, 13 (1.9%) Native American, 26 (3.9%) Asian, 130 (19.3%) from other races, and 21 (3.1%) from two or more races.  Hispanics or Latinos of any race were 193 people (28.7%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0673612|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715033333/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0673612|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Spreckels CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in noninstitutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

Of the 229 households, 89 (38.9%) had children under 18 living in them, 134 (58.5%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 27 (11.8%) had a female householder with no husband present, 12 (5.2%) had a male householder with no wife present, 7 (3.1%) were [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 2 (0.9%) were [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]; 45 households (19.7%) were one person and 17 (7.4%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.94.  There were 173 families (75.5% of households); the average family size was 3.38.

The age distribution was as follows: 172 people (25.6%) were under 18, 44 people (6.5%) were between 18 and 24, 173 people (25.7%) were between 25 and 44, 208 people (30.9%) were between 45 and 64, and 76 people (11.3%) were 65 or older. The median age was 39.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.9 males. Among those 18 and older, there were 92.7 males for every 100 females.

The 246 housing units had an average density of 2,013.8 per square mile; of the occupied units, 160 (69.9%) were owner-occupied and 69 (30.1%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 3.6%; the rental vacancy rate was 2.8%.  In all, 467 people (69.4% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 206 people (30.6%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median household income was $58,009 and the median family income was $51,250. Males had a median income of $22,250 versus $24,750 for females. The per capita income for the CDP was $19,752. None of the families and 1.1% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]], including none under 18 and none over 64.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

